# Kubernetes Bootstrap + Prometheus Deployment
Kubernetes bootstrap and monitoring setup using a DevOps best-practice approach. It leverages a Packer-built golden AMI and Terraform-provisioned infrastructure, followed by automated cluster initialization using kubeadm. Prometheus is deployed via a custom Helm chart with separated ConfigMaps for configuration and alert rules, enabling dynamic updates and observability validation. The included scripts provide a reproducible, step-by-step workflow for provisioning, deployment, and verification in a consistent and automated manner.

## Steps
1. Initialize cluster
2. Configure kubectl
3. Install CNI (Calico)
4. Install Helm
5. Deploy Prometheus
6. Update ConfigMap
7. Verify

## Usage
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
sudo yum install -y git
git clone https://github.com/RodzonLimjapV/k8s-bootstrap-repo-prometheus-chart.git

chmod +x scripts/*.sh

./scripts/01-init-cluster.sh
./scripts/02-configure-kubectl.sh
./scripts/03-install-cni.sh
./scripts/04-install-helm.sh
./scripts/05-deploy-prometheus.sh
 kubectl taint nodes --all node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane-
 kubectl get pods -n monitoring
 kubectl get svc -n monitoring
./scripts/06-update-configmap.sh
./scripts/07-verify.sh

http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:30090
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:30090/alerts



